1
00:00:30,125 --> 00:00:31,458
[KYON]
Okay.

2
00:00:31,541 --> 00:00:33,083
Asking somebody how long they've
believed in Santa Claus

3
00:00:33,166 --> 00:00:35,083
is so stupid,
you can't even consider it

4
00:00:35,166 --> 00:00:38,041
a topic suitable for
idle conversation.

5
00:00:38,125 --> 00:00:39,625
But if you still
wanna know how long

6
00:00:39,708 --> 00:00:42,416
I've believe in some old, fat
guy who wears a funky red suit,

7
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,166
I can tell you this:

8
00:00:44,250 --> 00:00:47,583
I've never believed
in him... ever.

9
00:00:47,666 --> 00:00:49,000
The Santa that showed up at my

10
00:00:49,083 --> 00:00:51,750
kindergarten Christmas festival?
I knew he was fake.

11
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:54,708
And I never saw Mommy
kissing Santa or anything.

12
00:00:54,791 --> 00:00:56,958
But I have to say that
even as a little kid,

13
00:00:57,041 --> 00:00:58,916
I knew better than to
believe in some old man

14
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:01,000
that only worked one day a year.

15
00:01:01,083 --> 00:01:03,458
Now, having said that,
it wasn't until I got older

16
00:01:03,541 --> 00:01:07,208
that I realized aliens, time
travelers, ghosts, monsters,

17
00:01:07,291 --> 00:01:08,666
ESPers, evil syndicates,

18
00:01:08,750 --> 00:01:11,375
and the anime slash manga
slash fantasy-flick heroes

19
00:01:11,458 --> 00:01:14,708
that fight said evil
syndicates... were also fake.

20
00:01:14,791 --> 00:01:17,250
Okay, I guess I always knew
those things were bogus,

21
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:18,750
I just didn't want to admit it.

22
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:21,833
All I ever wanted was for an
alien, time traveler, ghost,

23
00:01:21,916 --> 00:01:24,583
monster, ESPer, evil syndicate
or the hero who fought 'em

24
00:01:24,666 --> 00:01:27,375
to just appear and say, "Hey."

25
00:01:27,458 --> 00:01:30,500
Unfortunately, reality
is a hard road indeed.

26
00:01:30,583 --> 00:01:32,500
Yep, you gotta admit,
the laws of physics

27
00:01:32,583 --> 00:01:34,416
definitely puts
a damper on things.

28
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:36,000
I even stopped
watching those TV shows

29
00:01:36,083 --> 00:01:38,125
about aliens and
ghosts and stuff.

30
00:01:38,208 --> 00:01:41,458
Aliens, time travelers, ESPers,
'course they don't exist.

31
00:01:41,541 --> 00:01:43,791
But a little part of me
wishes that they did.

32
00:01:43,875 --> 00:01:45,333
I guess I've grown up
and realized

33
00:01:45,416 --> 00:01:46,750
that I can think
about those things

34
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:49,208
and still accept reality.

35
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,000
[KYON] But by the time
I got out of junior high,

36
00:01:53,083 --> 00:01:55,166
I pretty much outgrew
that kinda stuff.

37
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:56,458
And I guess I got
used to the idea of

38
00:01:56,541 --> 00:01:58,500
living in an ordinary world.

39
00:01:58,583 --> 00:02:01,083
And just like that--
I was in high school.

40
00:02:01,166 --> 00:02:03,500
And that's when I met her...

41
00:02:06,291 --> 00:02:09,541
I'm Haruhi Suzumiya
from East Junior High.

42
00:02:09,625 --> 00:02:12,583
First off, I'm not interested
in ordinary people.

43
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:15,916
But if any of you are aliens,
time travelers, or ESPers,

44
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:19,250
please come see me. That is all.

45
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:24,583
[KYON]
Is that supposed to be funny?

46
00:02:26,583 --> 00:02:29,625
[KYON] There stood before me
this amazing, beautiful girl.

47
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:35,166
Uh...

48
00:02:36,791 --> 00:02:39,458
[gasping]

49
00:02:39,541 --> 00:02:41,000
O-kay... Next?

50
00:02:41,083 --> 00:02:43,333
[KYON] I bet everyone
thought she was kidding,

51
00:02:43,416 --> 00:02:44,750
but it wasn't a joke.

52
00:02:44,833 --> 00:02:46,791
And it wasn't anything
to laugh about.

53
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:50,333
Haruhi is always dead serious.

54
00:02:50,416 --> 00:02:52,583
And that's how we first met.

55
00:02:52,666 --> 00:02:56,541
Looking back, I wanna believe
that it was just a coincidence.

56
00:04:28,958 --> 00:04:31,625
[KYON] As long as Haruhi
Suzumiya is sitting quietly,

57
00:04:31,708 --> 00:04:33,833
she's just like any other
extremely beautiful

58
00:04:33,916 --> 00:04:35,541
high school girl.

59
00:04:35,625 --> 00:04:38,250
And my seat just happens
to be in front of her.

60
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:39,958
I mean, can you
blame me for wanting

61
00:04:40,041 --> 00:04:43,333
to exploit this seating
arrangement so I could, um...

62
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:44,625
get to know her better?

63
00:04:44,708 --> 00:04:46,500
Hey, that stuff you were
saying when you were

64
00:04:46,583 --> 00:04:50,333
introducing yourself,
were you serious about all that?

65
00:04:50,416 --> 00:04:51,916
What about the stuff
I was saying?

66
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,375
[KYON] Well, you know,
about aliens and stuff.

67
00:04:54,458 --> 00:04:56,166
Why? Are you an alien
or something?

68
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:57,333
[KYON]
Well, no, but I just--

69
00:04:57,416 --> 00:04:59,458
Well, no, but you just what?

70
00:04:59,541 --> 00:05:01,000
Well, I-- Just forget it.

71
00:05:01,083 --> 00:05:02,833
Then why are we even
talking right now?

72
00:05:02,916 --> 00:05:05,375
You're wasting my time. Ugh.

73
00:05:09,041 --> 00:05:09,458
[KYON]
Hmm?

74
00:05:09,541 --> 00:05:10,625
[chuckling]

75
00:05:10,708 --> 00:05:11,958
[KYON]
Later on,

76
00:05:12,041 --> 00:05:13,291
I found out that quite
a few of my new classmates

77
00:05:13,375 --> 00:05:16,000
were from the same
junior high as Haruhi.

78
00:05:16,083 --> 00:05:17,750
[TANIGUCHI] Look, if you've
got the hots for her,

79
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:19,208
take my advice:

80
00:05:19,291 --> 00:05:20,625
Forget it.

81
00:05:20,708 --> 00:05:23,125
After being in the same class
as her for three years,

82
00:05:23,208 --> 00:05:25,291
I know her pretty well.

83
00:05:25,375 --> 00:05:28,208
Let's just say she's what you
might call beyond eccentric.

84
00:05:28,291 --> 00:05:29,416
Like her introduction?

85
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,708
Yep! In junior high,
I can't remember a day

86
00:05:31,791 --> 00:05:34,583
when she wasn't doing
something completely wacky.

87
00:05:34,666 --> 00:05:36,833
You ever hear the quad
scribbles incident?

88
00:05:36,916 --> 00:05:38,375
No, what's that?

89
00:05:38,458 --> 00:05:40,625
You know that thing that draws
lines on the athletic field?

90
00:05:40,708 --> 00:05:42,458
Agh, what d'ya call
that thing again?

91
00:05:42,541 --> 00:05:44,541
Whatever. Well, she used
that thing to draw

92
00:05:44,625 --> 00:05:47,000
this big, mysterious symbol
on the school quad.

93
00:05:47,083 --> 00:05:49,541
She snuck into the school
grounds at night to draw it.

94
00:05:49,625 --> 00:05:52,208
Yeah, I remember
reading about that.

95
00:05:52,291 --> 00:05:55,000
I think it was in the local
section of the daily newspaper.

96
00:05:55,083 --> 00:05:56,583
It sorta looked like
a botched version

97
00:05:56,666 --> 00:05:58,083
of a Nazca drawing, didn't it?

98
00:05:58,166 --> 00:06:00,625
[KYON] So, you're telling me
she did this all by herself?

99
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:03,333
[TANIGUCHI] No doubt. And she
totally admitted doing it.

100
00:06:03,416 --> 00:06:06,083
Oh yeah, and then one morning,
I get to class early.

101
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:08,500
All the desks were
shoved out into the hall!

102
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:10,958
Then there's the time she
painted a star on the roof.

103
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:12,708
And this other time when she
plastered these talismans...

104
00:06:12,791 --> 00:06:14,583
[KYON]
What the hell's she doing...?

105
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:15,833
[TANIGUCHI]
You know,

106
00:06:15,916 --> 00:06:17,041
like the ones you use
to reanimate corpses?

107
00:06:17,125 --> 00:06:18,875
I have no idea why.

108
00:06:18,958 --> 00:06:21,666
But all the same, man, she's
pretty popular with the guys.

109
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:23,666
She's not too hard
to look at, you know?

110
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:25,500
And she's freakin'
good at sports.

111
00:06:25,583 --> 00:06:27,666
And, on top of that,
she gets good grades.

112
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:29,125
She's a super weirdo.

113
00:06:29,208 --> 00:06:31,750
But if she's standing there
quietly, you'd never know.

114
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:34,000
[KUNIKIDA] Somethin' tells me
you have more to say about her.

115
00:06:34,083 --> 00:06:35,250
[TANIGUCHI]
For a while,

116
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:36,958
