to Haruhi Suzumiya.

196
00:09:43,125 --> 00:09:44,375
So when did you notice?

197
00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:46,625
[KYON]
Mmm... A while ago.

198
00:09:46,708 --> 00:09:48,916
Oh, I see.

199
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,375
Actually, I have this theory
that each day of the week

200
00:09:51,458 --> 00:09:53,375
has its own image
with a specific color

201
00:09:53,458 --> 00:09:56,833
that only goes with that day.
And by colors, I'd say...

202
00:09:56,916 --> 00:09:58,541
[KYON] It felt almost
like we were having a

203
00:09:58,625 --> 00:10:00,500
real conversation
for the first time.

204
00:10:00,583 --> 00:10:02,708
...and Thursday's green.
Friday is gold,

205
00:10:02,791 --> 00:10:05,875
and Saturday is brown. And
the color for Sunday is white.

206
00:10:05,958 --> 00:10:08,541
[KYON] Hey, I kinda understand
what she's talking about.

207
00:10:08,625 --> 00:10:10,583
[KYON] So, if you
turn that into numbers,

208
00:10:10,666 --> 00:10:13,250
Monday'd be zero, and
Sunday'd be six, right?

209
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:14,791
Right.

210
00:10:14,875 --> 00:10:17,958
[KYON] I kinda feel that
Monday's more like a one.

211
00:10:18,041 --> 00:10:20,625
I don't think anybody was
asking for your opinion.

212
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:22,833
[KYON]
Oh, is that so?

213
00:10:28,666 --> 00:10:29,666
[KYON]
Hm.

214
00:10:36,625 --> 00:10:38,125
Have I met you somewhere before?

215
00:10:38,208 --> 00:10:40,583
Like, maybe in the past,
or something like that?

216
00:10:40,666 --> 00:10:41,666
Not likely.

217
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:43,000
[exhales]

218
00:10:43,083 --> 00:10:44,875
[KYON] Usually, an event
is triggered by something

219
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:46,583
that's considered trivial.

220
00:10:46,666 --> 00:10:48,666
Well, this must've
been my trigger.

221
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:50,666
I was surprised that
Haruhi even replied

222
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:52,125
with a half-decent answer.

223
00:10:52,208 --> 00:10:53,708
I totally thought she'd
say something like,

224
00:10:53,791 --> 00:10:55,666
"

225
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:58,208
I mean, you get the picture...

226
00:11:00,166 --> 00:11:02,500
[KYON] And so, when Haruhi
came to class the next day

227
00:11:02,583 --> 00:11:04,541
with her long hair
all chopped off,

228
00:11:04,625 --> 00:11:06,791
I was rather disturbed by it.

229
00:11:06,875 --> 00:11:08,416
I mean, cutting
it short like that

230
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:10,250
the day after I
made my comment...

231
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:13,416
It's a little rash,
don't you think?

232
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:14,791
Not really.

233
00:11:16,291 --> 00:11:17,625
[KYON]
Ever since that day,

234
00:11:17,708 --> 00:11:19,458
talking to Haruhi right
before homeroom started

235
00:11:19,541 --> 00:11:21,458
was becoming sort of a ritual.

236
00:11:21,541 --> 00:11:25,000
[KYON] Is it true you've dumped
every guy you've ever dated?

237
00:11:25,083 --> 00:11:26,375
And just what
gives you the right

238
00:11:26,458 --> 00:11:28,750
to ask me a question like that?

239
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:30,833
I don't know about
anything you've heard.

240
00:11:30,916 --> 00:11:33,791
Whatever. You wanna believe it?
It's probably true.

241
00:11:33,875 --> 00:11:36,166
Well, with all that dating,
wasn't there at least one guy

242
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:37,833
