little serious about?

243
00:11:37,916 --> 00:11:39,000
Absolutely not.

244
00:11:39,083 --> 00:11:41,083
They all took themselves
way too seriously,

245
00:11:41,166 --> 00:11:44,208
and not even one of those dorks
was an alien, time traveler,

246
00:11:44,291 --> 00:11:45,583
or even an ESPer.

247
00:11:45,666 --> 00:11:46,958
[KYON]
That's how people are normally.

248
00:11:47,041 --> 00:11:48,333
Okay, so what's
with most of them

249
00:11:48,416 --> 00:11:49,875
asking me out over the phone?

250
00:11:49,958 --> 00:11:51,500
I mean, shouldn't important
stuff like that

251
00:11:51,583 --> 00:11:53,750
be done face-to-face,
not phone-to-phone?

252
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:55,041
Yeah, I mean, if it were me...

253
00:11:55,125 --> 00:11:58,083
[KYON] I'll just agree
with her for now.

254
00:11:58,166 --> 00:12:00,125
Yeah, well, none of that's
important anyway!

255
00:12:00,208 --> 00:12:01,375
[KYON]
So what is?

256
00:12:01,458 --> 00:12:02,583
Here's the problem:

257
00:12:02,666 --> 00:12:04,666
So far, the way it looks
is that all the men

258
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:06,833
in this entire universe
are pathetic.

259
00:12:06,916 --> 00:12:08,208
I mean, all through
junior high,

260
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:10,541
that was the one thing that
irritated me the most.

261
00:12:10,625 --> 00:12:12,125
All right then,
so what kind of guy

262
00:12:12,208 --> 00:12:14,166
would you have really have been
into? An alien or something?

263
00:12:14,250 --> 00:12:15,750
[HARUHI]
Yeah! Anything like an alien

264
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:17,666
or something else
along those lines.

265
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:20,291
Anyway, as long as the person
isn't an ordinary human,

266
00:12:20,375 --> 00:12:21,791
I don't care if it's
a boy or a girl.

267
00:12:21,875 --> 00:12:23,583
Hang on a sec,
what's wrong with being human?

268
00:12:23,666 --> 00:12:26,500
I mean, why do they
have to be an alien?

269
00:12:26,583 --> 00:12:30,291
Because that way,
life's more interesting.

270
00:12:32,041 --> 00:12:35,333
[school bell chimes]

271
00:12:36,458 --> 00:12:38,458
[KYON sighs]

272
00:12:40,291 --> 00:12:41,750
Hey, Kyon!

273
00:12:41,833 --> 00:12:43,750
You need to tell me what kind
of magic spell you're using.

274
00:12:43,833 --> 00:12:45,083
[KYON]
What're you talking about?

275
00:12:45,166 --> 00:12:47,666
I have never seen Suzumiya
talk that long before,

276
00:12:47,750 --> 00:12:49,416
and I'm not exaggerating, man!

277
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:51,166
What the hell'd you say to her?

278
00:12:51,250 --> 00:12:52,250
[KYON]
Huh...

279
00:12:52,333 --> 00:12:54,041
Wonder what I could've
said to her.

280
00:12:54,125 --> 00:12:56,125
I think it was all
pretty random stuff.

281
00:12:56,208 --> 00:12:57,750
This is a phenomenon.

282
00:12:57,833 --> 00:12:59,708
Kyon's always gone after
the strange ones;

283
00:12:59,791 --> 00:13:01,333
the weirder the better.

284
00:13:01,416 --> 00:13:03,666
Little louder, please,
so everyone can hear you.

285
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:05,791
[ASAKURA]
I wanna know how you did it.

286
00:13:05,875 --> 00:13:07,583
No matter how much
I've tried to talk to her,

287
00:13:07,666 --> 00:13:10,708
I can't get Haruhi to answer
any of my questions.

288
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:12,583
What do you do to
get her to open up?

289
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:13,916
Do you have any tips for me?

290
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,250
No idea.

291
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:17,875
[ASAKURA] Hmm... Still,
I think it's a good thing.

292
00:13:17,958 --> 00:13:20,000
I've been sorta worried
about her always being

293
00:13:20,083 --> 00:13:21,583
completely alone in our class.

294
00:13:21,666 --> 00:13:25,000
I think it's really great she's
made at least one friend here.

295
00:13:25,083 --> 00:13:27,208
A friend, huh?

296
00:13:27,291 --> 00:13:29,291
Well, just keep doing
whatever you're doing,

297
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:31,416
cause maybe she'll warm
up to the rest of us.

298
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,166
I mean, since we're all
in the same class,

299
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:35,208
it'd be really for the best
if everyone got a long,

300
00:13:35,291 --> 00:13:36,583
and that's why
I'm counting on you.

301
00:13:36,666 --> 00:13:37,583
[KYON]
Easy for you to say.

302
00:13:37,666 --> 00:13:38,791
In fact, from now on,

303
00:13:38,875 --> 00:13:40,166
if there's anything we
need to say to her,

304
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:42,916
we'll just talk to you,
and you can tell her for us.

305
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,125
[growls]

306
00:13:44,208 --> 00:13:46,041
Hey, hang on a sec!
What do ya think I am;

307
00:13:46,125 --> 00:13:48,875
am I supposed to be your
spokesperson or something?!

308
00:13:48,958 --> 00:13:50,666
Pretty please?

309
00:13:55,541 --> 00:13:57,291
[giggling]

310
00:13:58,541 --> 00:13:59,791
[gasps]

311
00:13:59,875 --> 00:14:02,125
Kyon, we're buddies, aren't we?
We're pals, right?

312
00:14:02,208 --> 00:14:04,750
[KYON]
Everyone's turned into an idiot.

313
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:06,750
Apparently we're changing seats.

314
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:09,083
I picked a number out of a
cookie tin that gave me the seat

315
00:14:09,166 --> 00:14:10,916
next to the window
second from the back.

316
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:13,208
An awesome seat if I may say so.

317
00:14:13,291 --> 00:14:17,208
Farewell, Haruhi. Forever.

318
00:14:17,291 --> 00:14:19,041
Coincidence?

319
00:14:19,708 --> 00:14:22,375
[KYON] Hey, I heard you checked
out all the clubs at school.

320
00:14:22,458 --> 00:14:24,041
Give me a heads up
if you know about

321
00:14:24,125 --> 00:14:26,416
any interesting ones, okay?

322
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:27,791
Absolutely none.

323
00:14:27,875 --> 00:14:29,041
[KYON]
An instant reply.

324
00:14:29,125 --> 00:14:30,583
Absolutely none!

325
00:14:30,666 --> 00:14:33,458
[KYON] It seems she likes to use
the word "absolutely" a lot.

326
00:14:33,541 --> 00:14:35,083
I thought things would
get a little better

327
00:14:35,166 --> 00:14:37,333
when I got into highschool,
but it's the same here

328
00:14:37,416 --> 00:14:40,041
as it's been throughout all
these mandatory school years.

329
00:14:40,125 --> 00:14:42,291
Maybe I'm just in
the wrong school.

330
00:14:42,375 --> 00:14:45,333
[KYON] I sorta wonder
what her criteria are.

331
00:14:45,416 --> 00:14:47,916
There was a club called the
"Mystery Research Club."

332
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,291
[KYON]
Yeah? How was that?

333
00:14:49,375 --> 00:14:51,375
It was hilarious.
They told me they've never

334
00:14:51,458 --> 00:14:53,833
had anything they could
even remotely call a case.

335
00:14:53,916 --> 00:14:56,750
And the members were a bunch
of mystery novel otakus.

336
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:58,791
Definitely not
master detectives.

337
00:14:58,875 --> 00:14:59,916
[KYON]
Well, that figures.

338
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,500
Yeah, well I had high hopes for

339
00:15:01,583 --> 00:15:04,083
the Supernatural Phenomenon
Research Club, too,

340
00:15:04,166 --> 00:15:06,458
but that thing was just
a bunch of occult freaks.

341
00:15:06,541 --> 00:15:07,583
What do you think of it?

342
00:15:07,666 --> 00:15:08,541
I don't think about it.

343
00:15:08,625 --> 00:15:10,583
Oh man! I'm so bored!

344
00:15:10,666 --> 00:15:12,541
With all these clubs, you'd
think they're be a couple of

345
00:15:12,625 --> 00:15:14,500
really strange cool
ones out there.

346
00:15:14,583 --> 00:15:16,291
Listen, you can't help
it if there aren't any.

347
00:15:16,375 --> 00:15:18,500
Besides, us normal human types,
we gotta be happy

348
00:15:18,583 --> 00:15:20,958
with what we're given, you know
what I'm saying?

349
00:15:21,041 --> 00:15:22,500
You could look at it this way:

350
00:15:22,583 --> 00:15:24,250
the people who don't like what
they got are the same people

351
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:25,791
who invent things
and make discoveries

352
00:15:25,875 --> 00:15:27,166
and advance civilization.

353
00:15:27,250 --> 00:15:29,083
They made airplanes 'cause
they wanted to fly,

354
00:15:29,166 --> 00:15:31,041
and they made cars and trains
'cause they wanted to go

355
00:15:31,125 --> 00:15:33,625
from place to place.
It's as simple as that.

356
00:15:33,708 --> 00:15:36,125
The only reason that we've got
all the things we have now

357
00:15:36,208 --> 00:15:38,125
is because a certain group
of people got together

358
00:15:38,208 --> 00:15:39,916
and used their talent
or imagination

359
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,000
or genius or whatever
to make it all possible.

360
00:15:42,083 --> 00:15:44,250
Ordinary people are
probably better off

361
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:45,666
living their ordinary,
little lives

362
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:46,583
in an ordinary manner.

363
00:15:46,666 --> 00:15:47,916
Shut up.

364
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,208
[KYON]
Hmm?

365
00:15:49,291 --> 00:15:50,333
[growls]

366
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:53,416
[KYON]
Perhaps it was this conversation

367
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:55,208
that sparked the idea...

368
00:15:56,958 --> 00:15:59,083
[KYON]
It happened suddenly.

369
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:02,041
[grunts]

370
00:16:02,125 --> 00:16:04,458
[whimpers]

371
00:16:04,541 --> 00:16:05,583
What's wrong with you?!

372
00:16:05,666 --> 00:16:06,916
I got an idea!

373
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,083
About what?

374
00:16:08,166 --> 00:16:10,250
I can't believe I didn't
realize it before!

375
00:16:10,333 --> 00:16:11,500
It's so obvious!

376
00:16:11,583 --> 00:16:12,875
What is?

377
00:16:12,958 --> 00:16:15,041
If it doesn't exist,
I should just make it myself!

378
00:16:15,125 --> 00:16:16,458
Make what yourself?

379
00:16:16,541 --> 00:16:18,041
Make a club!

380
00:16:18,125 --> 00:16:20,833
[sighs]

381
00:16:20,916 --> 00:16:23,333
I hear ya, but you gotta
calm down, all right?

382
00:16:23,416 --> 00:16:25,375
What's with you?! This is
what we're talkin' about!

383
00:16:25,458 --> 00:16:27,833
You should be happy you're
about this development.

384
00:16:27,916 --> 00:16:30,541
Well... we're in the
middle of class.

385
00:16:30,625 --> 00:16:33,041
[chuckles nervously]

386
00:16:33,125 --> 00:16:34,000
Hmm?

387
00:16:36,250 --> 00:16:39,958
[school bell chimes]

388
00:16:40,041 --> 00:16:41,500
You're gonna help.

389
00:16:41,583 --> 00:16:44,083
[KYON] I feel like I'm being
bullied outta my lunch money.

390
00:16:44,166 --> 00:16:45,125
What d'ya need help with?

391
00:16:45,208 --> 00:16:47,250
Starting my new club,
that's what!

392
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:48,958
First, tell me why I'm the
one who's gotta help you

393
00:16:49,041 --> 00:16:51,250
set up a club that's your
idea in the first place.

394
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:52,666
And you can let go
of the tie, now.

395
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:54,541
I'll find us a room
and some members,

396
00:16:54,625 --> 00:16:56,833
and I want you to personally
handle all the paperwork...

397
00:16:56,916 --> 00:16:58,791
[KYON]
She's not listening.

398
00:16:58,875 --> 00:17:01,250
Why don't you tell me what
kind of club it's gonna be.

399
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:03,000
[HARUHI]
Who cares about that right now?!

400
00:17:03,083 --> 00:17:04,750
We've gotta go
make the club first!

401
00:17:04,833 --> 00:17:07,875
You got it? Do all that stuff
before school ends today.

402
00:17:07,958 --> 00:17:09,916
I'll find a room for
the club by then!

403
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,541
Okie-dokie?

404
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:16,666
[KYON] Rules for the creation of
a new extra-curricular group...

405
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:19,041
At least five members,
a teacher to supervise,

406
00:17:19,125 --> 00:17:21,708
a name, the name of
the person in charge,

407
00:17:21,791 --> 00:17:23,541
the purpose of the organization.

408
00:17:23,625 --> 00:17:25,333
There's nothing for me to do.

409
00:17:25,416 --> 00:17:27,916
It's all in the back of
the student handbook.

410
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,666
And I can bet money on this:

411
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,916
Haruhi's little scheme?
Nothing about it's gonna

412
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,708
contribute to making school life
more creative or more fun.

413
00:17:34,791 --> 00:17:36,583
Of that I'm positive.

414
00:17:39,875 --> 00:17:42,541
This is going to be
our new clubroom!

415
00:17:42,625 --> 00:17:45,583
[KYON] Hang on, I don't even
know where we are right now.

416
00:17:45,666 --> 00:17:47,583
This is the cultural department!

417
00:17:47,666 --> 00:17:49,208
The art club's got the art room,

418
00:17:49,291 --> 00:17:52,583
and the wind ensemble has got
the music room, am I right?

419
00:17:52,666 --> 00:17:55,000
Club's that don't need
specialized classrooms like that

420
00:17:55,083 --> 00:17:57,416
end up in this wing of
the cultural department.

421
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:59,500
They call it the old building.

422
00:17:59,583 --> 00:18:01,041
This room's for
the literary club.

423
00:18:01,125 --> 00:18:02,875
[KYON] So then it's the
literary club's room.

424
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:05,125
Yeah, I know, I know,
but this past spring

425
00:18:05,208 --> 00:18:08,708
all the senior members left, so
now the club's got no members.

426
00:18:08,791 --> 00:18:11,875
And if nobody else joins,
then that club's gonna be cut.

427
00:18:11,958 --> 00:18:15,458
Oh, and this girl's
a new freshman member.

428
00:18:15,541 --> 00:18:17,500
[KYON] So, the club
hasn't been cut then.

429
00:18:17,583 --> 00:18:18,791
It's the same difference.

430
00:18:18,875 --> 00:18:20,708
Besides, she's
the only one here.

431
00:18:20,791 --> 00:18:22,333
But what're we gonna
do with her?

432
00:18:22,416 --> 00:18:24,208
She told me that
she wouldn't mind it.

433
00:18:24,291 --> 00:18:25,583
You sure about that?

434
00:18:25,666 --> 00:18:27,291
[HARUHI] When I saw her
at lunch, I asked her

435
00:18:27,375 --> 00:18:28,708
if we could use the club room.

436
00:18:28,791 --> 00:18:30,958
She said go ahead.
She doesn't really care as long

437
00:18:31,041 --> 00:18:32,916
as she has a place to read.

438
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,625
I guess some folks are just
strange like that, you know?

439
00:18:35,708 --> 00:18:37,208
[KYON]
Look who's talking...

440
00:18:39,666 --> 00:18:41,541
Yuki Nagato...

441
00:18:42,708 --> 00:18:44,416
[KYON]
Miss... Nagato, was it?

442
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:46,750
You understand my colleague
here wants to use this room

443
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:49,541
for some other type of club.
Are you okay with that?

444
00:18:49,625 --> 00:18:50,375
I'm fine.

445
00:18:50,458 --> 00:18:51,625
You are?

446
00:18:51,708 --> 00:18:53,125
O-Okay, but I'm pretty
sure we're gonna end up

447
00:18:53,208 --> 00:18:54,666
causing you a lot
of trouble though.

448
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:56,000
No problem.

449
00:18:56,083 --> 00:18:58,000
But someday you might get
kicked out of this room.

450
00:18:58,083 --> 00:18:59,458
Go ahead.

451
00:19:00,625 --> 00:19:02,083
[HARUHI]
Well, there you have it!

452
00:19:02,166 --> 00:19:04,250
From now on, we're gonna
meet here in this room

453
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:05,625
right after school.

454
00:19:05,708 --> 00:19:07,708
And ya better show up, mister,
'cause if you don't

455
00:19:07,791 --> 00:19:09,833
it's the death penalty!

456
00:19:09,916 --> 00:19:11,083
Understood.

457
00:19:11,791 --> 00:19:13,333
[KYON]
I don't wanna die.

458
00:19:13,416 --> 00:19:15,500
We need to find club members.

459
00:19:15,583 --> 00:19:17,916
We're gonna need at
least two more people.

460
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,583
[KYON] What, that means
you already have that

461
00:19:19,666 --> 00:19:21,875
literary club girl included
in the head count?

462
00:19:21,958 --> 00:19:23,833
Does Haruhi think she
comes with the room

463
00:19:23,916 --> 00:19:25,750
like some kind of accessory?

464
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:27,833
Don't worry,
I'll get 'em in no time.

465
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:30,500
I gotta couple leads on some
random people I can bring in.

466
00:19:30,583 --> 00:19:31,416
[school bell chimes]

467
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:33,041
[KYON]
And so, the next day...

468
00:19:33,125 --> 00:19:34,791
I'll meet ya there!

469
00:19:36,666 --> 00:19:38,625
[KYON]
I guess I had no choice.

470
00:19:38,708 --> 00:19:41,458
I found myself shuffling
over to the club room.

471
00:19:43,208 --> 00:19:45,500
[KYON]
So, whatcha readin'?

472
00:19:47,208 --> 00:19:48,958
[KYON]
Is it interesting?

473
00:19:51,291 --> 00:19:52,458
Unique.

474
00:19:52,541 --> 00:19:55,375
[KYON]
So, what part's unique?

475
00:19:55,458 --> 00:19:56,625
All of it.

476
00:19:56,708 --> 00:19:58,833
[KYON]
Huh, you really like books.

477
00:20:01,083 --> 00:20:02,125
A little...

478
00:20:02,208 --> 00:20:03,375
[KYON]
I see...

479
00:20:05,958 --> 00:20:08,166
Can I go home now?

480
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:11,333
Sorry about that!

481
00:20:11,416 --> 00:20:12,791
I'm a little late today
'cause it took me

482
00:20:12,875 --> 00:20:14,750
forever to catch her.

483
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:17,333
[KYON] It was another girl.
A really beautiful girl.

484
00:20:17,416 --> 00:20:20,166
What is this? Where am I?

485
00:20:20,250 --> 00:20:22,083
W-Why did you bring me here?

486
00:20:22,166 --> 00:20:24,916
Who are you people anyway?

487
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,708
Why are you locking the door?!

488
00:20:26,791 --> 00:20:27,916
What do you want from me?!

489
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,333
[HARUHI]
Just be quiet.

490
00:20:31,250 --> 00:20:34,625
Allow me to introduce
